  "name": "Familial Hypercholesterolemia - Comprehensive Provider Query",
  "description": "Simulates a lipid clinic provider identifying their complete FH patient population. The Geisinger PheKB FH algorithm uses LDL ≥ 190, statin therapy adjustment, and ASCVD history scoring (Dutch Lipid Clinic Network criteria). Real-world FH identification primarily unions: FH diagnosis codes, statin prescriptions, and severely elevated LDL labs. Note that the statin query is broadly cross-indication — most statin patients don't have FH but do have other cardiovascular risk.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete familial hypercholesterolemia (FH) patient population for a genetic testing and cascade screening initiative. From clinical experience, FH patients are documented in different ways: many have a formal FH diagnosis code, most are on statin therapy, and some are undiagnosed but have very elevated LDL.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any FH diagnosis (parent, heterozygous, homozygous, or LDL receptor mutation variants)\n2. Patients prescribed statin therapy\n3. Patients with LDL cholesterol ≥ 190 mg/dL\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found. The statin query will substantially overcount — most statin patients are non-FH. The LDL query catches undiagnosed FH which is the most clinically valuable group for genetic testing referral.",
